table.name: gtm_transaction
table.description: Trade transaction. It also references a transportion object such as order release or shipment.

columns.name: GTM_TRANSACTION_GID
columns.description: The GID for the GTM trade transaction.

columns.name: GTM_TRANSACTION_XID
columns.description: The external identifier (XID) for the GTM trade transaction.

columns.name: DATA_QUERY_TYPE_GID
columns.description: A data query type represents different business objects.

columns.name: OBJECT_ID
columns.description: The object ID.

columns.name: INDICATOR
columns.description: Marks the condition or state of the GTM trade transaction using colors.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED1_ICON_GID
columns.description: Marks the condition or state of the GTM trade transaction using images. It is a foreign key reference to ICON table.

columns.name: CARRIER_CODE
columns.description: The carrier code.

columns.name: CONVEYANCE_NAME
columns.description: Name of the vessel used for the border movement GTM trade transaction.

columns.name: CONVEYANCE_FLAG
columns.description: Flag of the vessel used for the border movement GTM trade transaction.

columns.name: TRANSPORT_MODE_GID
columns.description: Transport mode used for the border movement GTM trade transaction. It is a foreign key reference to the TRANSPORT_MODE table.

columns.name: INCO_TERM_GID
columns.description: Incoterm used for the GTM trade transaction. It is a foreign key reference to the INCO_TERM table.

columns.name: MARKED_FOR_PURGE
columns.description: Indicates if the GTM trade transaction has been marked to be purged.

columns.name: INCO_TERM_LOCATION
columns.description: Incoterm location used for the GTM trade transaction.

columns.name: IS_HAZARDOUS_CARGO
columns.description: Indicates if the goods on the GTM trade transaction are hazardous.

columns.name: GTM_CONSOL_CRITERIA_GID
columns.description: N/A

columns.name: IS_SHIPMENT_CREATED
columns.description: Indicates if a GTM declaration has been created for this GTM trade transaction.

columns.name: GTM_TRANSACTION_TYPE
columns.description: Specifies if the object is a GTM trade transaction or a GTM declaration.

columns.name: GTM_TRANSACTION_TYPE_GID
columns.description: The transaction type ID across all domains. This is a foreign key to GTM_TRANSACTION_TYPE table.

columns.name: GTM_DECLARATION_TYPE_GID
columns.description: The declaration type ID across all domains. Which is a foreign key to GTM_DECLARATION_TYPE table.

columns.name: GTM_BOND_GID
columns.description: The bond or guarantee used for the import duties and taxes of the GTM trade transaction.

columns.name: REQ_BS_STATUS_GROUP_GID
columns.description: This column refers to the Status Group of the request status of custom filing of a declaration. It is a foreign key reference to the BS_STATUS_GROUP table.

columns.name: REQ_BS_STATUS_CODE_GID
columns.description: This column refers to the Status Code of the request for customs filing of a declaration. It is a foreign key reference to the BS_STATUS_CODE table.

columns.name: RESP_BS_STATUS_GROUP_GID
columns.description: This column refers to the Status Group of the response status received after custom filing of a declaration. It is a foreign key reference to the BS_STATUS_GROUP table.

columns.name: RESP_BS_STATUS_CODE_GID
columns.description: This column refers to the Status Code of the response received after customs filing of a declaration. It is a foreign key reference to the BS_STATUS_CODE table.

columns.name: GTM_DECL_S_TYPE_GID
columns.description: The Declaration Sub Type ID. It is foreign key reference to GTM_DECL_S_TYPE table.

columns.name: GTM_TRADE_PREFERENCE_GID
columns.description: The Trade Preference ID which is the tariff treatment of the goods. It is a foreign key reference to GTM_TRADE_PREFERENCE table.

columns.name: GTM_PROCEDURE_GID
columns.description: This is the customs procedure being requested for this declaration. Examples include Inward Processing Procedure in the EU or Consumption - Foreign Trade Zone in the US. It is a foreign key to GTM_PROCEDURE.

columns.name: GTM_PRIOR_PROCEDURE_GID
columns.description: Specifies the previous customs procedure that occurred before the current one. For example, before your goods are released for free circulation, they may have entered a bonded warehouse first. This field is used to indicate the entry into the bonded warehouse. It is a foreign key reference to GTM_PROCEDURE.

columns.name: GTM_PROCEDURE_DETAIL_GID
columns.description: The procedure detail GID.

columns.name: EXCHANGE_RATE_GID
columns.description: The Exchange Rate ID to be used for value conversion while preparing the declaration. It is foreign key reference to EXCHANGE_RATE table.

columns.name: EXCHANGE_RATE_DATE
columns.description: The Exchange Rate date to be used for value conversion while preparing the declaration.

columns.name: CURRENCY_GID
columns.description: The currency in which values should be sent for filing. It is foreign key reference to CURRENCY table.

columns.name: LOGIC_CONFIG_GID
columns.description: The declaration configuration details that were used to build declaration from transactions or transaction lines.

columns.name: INLAND_CONVEYANCE_NAME
columns.description: The inland conveyance name.

columns.name: INLAND_CONVEYANCE_FLAG
columns.description: The inland conveyance flag.

columns.name: INLAND_TRANSPORT_MODE_GID
columns.description: The inland transport mode. Which is a foreign key to TRANSPORT_MODE table.

columns.name: DEPARTURE_CONVEYANCE_NAME
columns.description: The departure conveyance name.

columns.name: DEPARTURE_CONVEYANCE_FLAG
columns.description: The departure conveyance flag.

columns.name: DEPART_TRANSPORT_MODE_GID
columns.description: The departure transport mode. Which is a foreign key to TRANSPORT_MODE table.

columns.name: GTM_VALUATION_METHOD_GID
columns.description: The valuation method ID.
